{
  "stem": "945.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I do remember seeing, after about a couple of hours, wagons with wounded Russian soldiers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When the bombs fell, they wounded many Russian soldiers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some of them were dead.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were carted in wagons by horses.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The blood was pouring out of the wagons.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I saw that, my own eyes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But that's not-- this is-- I'm just relating that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The story that I will never forget-- as we approached the center where the authorities were, I remember a Russian general [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] stood up on a platform and started to address the people.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And he started to speak in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And he said that he is from a certain city in Russia, which he had liberated, and didn't find anybody alive of his family or any other Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that our area was the first area where he started seeing Jewish people and recognized Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he said that all in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And my brother and I, we listened.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And immediately, of course, some Ukrainian population started protesting to the fact that he spoke Yiddish and told him [RUSSIAN].",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Well, he then started speaking in Russian, but he told us what we wanted to hear.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I'll never forget that, because having survived such a tragedy, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] words like that brought us encouragement and gave us some hope.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And told us that maybe the Jewish people will survive after all.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And so, we got liberated that early spring.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And within six weeks, we started making plans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We heard that the Russian army had advanced far enough for us to return home.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And so one day, we--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes, it was-- it started to be easier.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
